cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the approach of solving navigation tasks for robotic systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of cognitive approach and semiotic knowledge representation suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the methodology. The fact that a coalition of robots is involved in the task indicates the possibility of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) being relevant. The study of spatial and behavior interaction of robots suggests the involvement of control systems (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
